## New Features [Prio]
- [HIGH] Challange submission type: None: Basically you just need to check in, there is nothing to do. If a challange submission type is none, we should not show  the challange rich text editor, since nothing will be shown to the player, and it will be immediatly completed. We keep the completion info, since that the player can see once the base is completed.
- [HIGH] Send notifications to teams as operator from mobile.
- [HIGH] Pin dragging when setting the pin for a base is awful on web, not draggable, just clicking around and not very precise
- [MED] Show feedback to the teams after completing a challange, if feedback was added on the submission review.
- [MED] As admin pending invites stay forever, should be able to manually delete a pending invite, that link should then be invalid. We also show the operators list on top, so we also don't need the list of aproved invitations.
- [MED] The Overview and Dashboard tabs on the web, are quite pointless, they basically just show stats. The overview is important due to the go live button and checklist, but we can improve the rest. Maybe we show a base map, the checklist, base list, team list, all this things can be small
- [LOW] Individual mode (Where it's one player per team), for the user it is all just one thing. One join code for all?
- [LOW] Private matches, even with the code, you aprove who gets to join, a player joins and it shows the game locked(like when it has not started yet), until the operator aproves him.




